     <body>
     <div type="encomium">
   <head>To my friend, M<seg rend="sup">r</seg>. <hi>Ben: Ionson.</hi> vpon <hi>his Alchemist.</hi>
   </head>
   <lg>
      <l>
         <hi>A</hi> Master, read in flatteries great skill,</l>
      <l>Could not passe truth, though he would force his will,</l>
      <l>By praising this too much, to get more praise</l>
      <l>In his Art, then you out of yours doe raise.</l>
      <l>Nor can full truth be vttered of your worth,</l>
      <l>Vnlesse you your owne praises doe set forth:</l>
      <l>None else can write so skilfully, to shew</l>
      <l>Your praise: Ages shall pay, yet still must owe.</l>
      <l>All I dare say, is, you haue written well,</l>
      <l>In what exceeding height, I dare not tell.</l>
   </lg>
   <closer>
      <signed>George Lucy.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
